<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="65" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,766,1043]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,333,910,935]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Comments.</emphasis>
This species can be separated from the others by the predominantly metallic blue dorsal color and the short reddish stripe on the anterolateral margins of the pronotum; the ventral large red stripes contrasting with remaining dark metallic green or blue on its abdomen; the shape of the metasternal process; and the shape of the gonocoxite 
<number box="[282,298,1018,1042]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" value="8.0">8</number>
. In this species and 
<taxonomicName box="[523,665,1018,1042]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Edessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="splendens" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[523,665,1018,1042]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">E. splendens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[672,761,1019,1043]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[672,761,1019,1043]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
the humeral angles are longer than in 
<taxonomicName box="[1190,1317,1018,1042]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Edessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="preclara" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1190,1317,1018,1042]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">E. preclara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
